success%20%E2%80%94%20is%20crucial%20early%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-promotes-smallest-partner-class-years-consulting-slowdown-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%20defines%20sponsors%20as%20high-ranking%20employees%20who%20%26quot%3Boffer%20seniority%2C%20power%2C%20and%20influence%20to%20help%20you%20meet%20your%20goals.%26quot%3B%20They%20differ%20from%20formally%20assigned%20mentors%2C%20who%20assist%20with%20annual%20reviews%2C%20guidance%2C%20and%20emotional%20support.%20Instead%2C%20sponsor%20relationships%20are%20formed%20through%20more%20organic%20connections%20with%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B99%25%20of%20it%20is%20unofficial%2C%20and%20it's%20about%20finding%20people%20that%20you%20want%20to%20help%20basically%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matthew%20Fitzpatrick%2C%20a%20senior%20partner%20at%20McKinsey%20and%20global%20leader%20of%20the%20firm's%20AI%20division%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-ai-consulting-focus-future-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQuantumBlack%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Fitzpatrick%20has%20sponsored%20hundreds%20of%20employees%20during%20his%2012-year%20tenure%20at%20the%20firm%20and%20said%20it's%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20the%20most%20fun%20part%20of%20my%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20advice%20to%20younger%20employees%20is%20to%20seek%20sponsors%20who%20share%20their%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20good%20mentor%20and%20sponsorship%20relationships%20are%20built%20around%20really%20shared%20interests%20and%20passions%20for%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20relationships%20I%20formed%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20were%20people%20that%20were%20really%20interested%20in%20the%20same%20things%20I%20am.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20McKinsey%20consultants%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-partner-aamanh-sehdev-strategy-consulting-career-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvancing%20at%20the%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20tough%20without%20a%20sponsor.%20%26quot%3BSponsors%20are%20extremely%20important%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20are%20looking%20for%20your%20next%20promotion%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20associate%20who%20left%20last%20April%20told%20Business%20Insider%20by%20text.%20%26quot%3BThey%20can%20certainly%20make%20your%20career%20if%20you%20have%20strong%20sponsors%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20a%20strong%20sponsor%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20survive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20consultants%20work%20on%20a%20project-to-project%20basis%2C%20and%20sponsors%20can%20also%20help%20new%20hires%20secure%20projects%20that%20build%20their%20reputation%20within%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20first%20six%20to%20seven%20months%20when%20I%20was%20a%20brand%20new%20analyst%20at%20Accenture%2C%20it%20was%20just%20really%20tough%20to%20get%20onto%20high-quality%20projects%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20totally%20lost%2C%20even%20though%20I%20was%20assigned%20a%20career%20counselor%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20Accenture%20consultant%2C%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20to%20avoid%20jeopardizing%20career%20prospects%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20a%20breakthrough%20when%20a%20senior%20consultant%20at%20the%20firm%20recognized%20her%20potential%20and%20put%20her%20on%20his%20next%20project%2C%20which%20offered%20the%20kind%20of%20visibility%20she%20needed%20to%20advance%20her%20career%20at%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLiterally%20because%20of%20him%2C%20one%20good%20project%20led%20to%20another%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20became%20my%20biggest%20advocate%20in%20terms%20of%20being%20not%20only%20a%20sponsor%20for%20promotions%20but%20also%20a%20mentor%20for%20coaching%20me%20on%20the%20day-to-day.%26quot%3B%20Eventually%2C%20he%20became%20her%20direct%20manager%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20top%20consulting%20firms%20have%20various%20types%20of%20corporate%20mentorship%20programs%2C%20which%20are%20different%20from%20sponsors.%20These%20programs%20offer%20employees%20one-on-one%20guidance%20with%20senior-level%20executives.%20Some%20pair%20employees%20from%20different%20generations%20or%20demographic%20backgrounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20consultants%20say%20that%20mentorship%20alone%20can't%20fill%20the%20gap%20between%20success%20and%20failure%20at%20a%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Accenture%20consultant%20stayed%20at%20the%20firm%20for%20four%20years%20due%20to%20the%20support%20of%20her%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeyond%20the%20formal%20boss%20and%20employee%20relationship%2C%20he%20also%20made%20an%20extra%20effort%20to%20both%20mentor%20me%20and%20be%20my%20advocate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20distinction%20is%20important.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20people%20need%20individuals%20who%20are%20in%20both%20camps.%20Sometimes%2C%20you%20can't%20get%20both%20in%20one%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-firms-sponsors-secret-to-success-mckinsey-accenture-consultants-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737225706000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678b1720ae09223df2ba9896%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-firms-sponsors-secret-to-success-mckinsey-accenture-consultants-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Current%20and%20former%20consultants%20say%20you%20often%20need%20the%20support%20of%20a%20high-ranking%20executive%20with%20power%20and%20influence%20to%20succeed%20at%20the%20top%20firms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40insider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A42%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-firms-sponsors-secret-to-success-mckins