r.com%2Frussian-icbm-test-fail-hints-at-new-missile-problems-analysts-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecatastrophic%20failure%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20testing%20in%20September%2C%20with%20satellite%20imagery%20showing%20a%20big%20crater%20around%20the%20launchpad%20at%20the%20Plesetsk%20Cosmodrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20apparent%20failure%20followed%20what%20missile%20experts%20have%20described%20as%20a%20host%20of%20other%20issues.%20Ejection%20tests%20and%20its%20flight%20testing%20were%20repeatedly%20delayed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Frussias-sarmat-test-failure-implications-strategic-balance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20think%20tank%20in%20London%2C%20and%20it%20had%20at%20least%20two%20canceled%20flight%20tests%20and%20at%20least%20one%20other%20flight%20test%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sarmat%20is%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20Soviet-era%20R-36%2C%20which%20first%20entered%20service%20in%201988.%20NATO%20calls%20the%20long-range%20missile%2C%20which%20has%20been%20modified%20over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20SS-18%20%26quot%3BSatan.%26quot%3B%20Without%20the%20new%20Sarmat%2C%20Russia%20has%20to%20rely%20on%20older%20missiles%2C%20extending%20their%20lives%2C%20but%20that%20can't%20go%20on%20indefinitely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d91baa2-083b-4da8-a8dc-3564db95933b%5C%22%3EStuck%20with%20inferior%20missiles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDelays%20to%20the%20Sarmat%2C%20or%20even%20its%20cancellation%2C%20would%20mean%20Russia%20has%20to%20keep%20using%20older%20systems%20as%20nations%20like%20China%20field%20new%20DF-41%20ICBMs%20and%20the%20US%20pushes%20forward%20with%20upgrades%20for%20its%20ICBM%20force%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Sentinel%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20R-36%20is%20%26quot%3Balready%20really%2C%20really%20past%20its%20service%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Timothy%20Wright%2C%20a%20missile%20technology%20expert%20at%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%2C%20yet%20the%20Russians%20keep%20having%20to%20extend%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20said%20at%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%20they%20were%20going%20to%20be%20out%20of%20service%20by%202007%2C%20but%20here%20they%20are%2C%20still%20in%20operation%20nearly%20two%20decades%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20only%20so%20much%20they%20can%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%20%26quot%3BParts%20will%20start%20failing%20at%20some%20point.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20the%20R-36s%20%26quot%3Bwill%20eventually%20start%20failing%20because%20their%20parts%20just%20will%20need%20replacement%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20make%20the%20parts%20anymore.%26quot%3B%20If%20Moscow%20tried%20to%20launch%2040%20R-36s%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20might%20not%20get%20all%2040%20out%20the%20ground%2C%20frankly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Sarmat%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missil%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63f62f5e88f76900192cd176%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22822%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussia's%20Sarmat%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20is%20launched%20in%20Russia's%20northwest%20region%20of%20Plesetsk%20in%20April%202022.%3Cp%3ERoscosmos%20Space%20Agency%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFabian%20Hoffmann%2C%20a%20missile%20expert%20at%20the%20Oslo%20Nuclear%20Project%2C%20said%20the%20R-36%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bsitting%20there%20for%20a%20really%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20was%20required%20to%20reduce%20the%20size%20of%20its%20arsenal%20of%20missiles%20under%20the%20New%20START%20treaty%20with%20the%20US.%20Hoffman%20said%20that%20Russia%20could%20use%20old%20parts%20from%20those%20missiles%20to%20keep%20its%20usable%20ones%20running.%20But%20the%20supply%20is%20not%20infinite%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWho%20knows%20how%20much%20these%20missiles%20can%20still%20take%2C%20how%20many%20years%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20the%20possibility%20Russia%20would%20%26quot%3Bhave%20to%20start%20cannibalizing%20existing%20missiles%2C%20taking%20them%20out%20of%20service%20or%20retiring%20them%20or%20taking%20them%20off%20what%20they%20call%20combat%20duty%20alert%2C%20which%20is%20where%20the%20missile%20is%20literally%20ready%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20other%20ICBMs%2C%20but%20the%20R-36%20carries%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20strategically%20significant%20payload.%20The%20Sarmat%2C%20as%20its%20replacement%2C%20will%20likewise%20carry%20a%20substantial%20payload.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c98c0ba2-0080-4768-8fd9-052109cb6939%5C%22%3EBig%20missiles%20with%20lots%20of%20warheads%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20purpose%20of%20the%20Sarmat%20was%20%26quot%3Bto%20constitute%20a%20big%20bulk%20of%20their%20warheads%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20ICBM%20is%20a%20large%2C%20long-range%20weapon%20able%20to%20carry%20a%20heavy%20MIRV%20payload%2C%20meaning%20multiple%20independent%20re-entry%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sarmat%20has%20an%20estimated%20maximum%20range%20of%2018%2C000%20miles.%20It%20has%20a%20ten-ton%20payload%20and%20can%20carry%2010%20large%20warheads%20or%2016%20smaller%20ones%2C%20per%20a%20Missile%20Threat%20fact%20sheet%20from%20the%20Center%20of%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies.%20The%20R-36%20it%20is%20meant%20to%20replace%20has%20a%20shorter%20range%20but%20similar%20payload%2C%20able%20to%20carry%2010%20multiple%20independent%20re-entry%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20grey%20missile%20is%20seen%20on%20its%20side%20resting%20on%20supports%20above%20a%20tarmac%20and%20grass%20ground%20and%20a%20grey%20s